Forte Oil of Nigeria Falls as First-Quarter Profit Drops 73%

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-08-04T15:26:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/forte-oil-of-nigeria-falls-as-first-quarter-profit-drops-73-.html
Forte Oil Plc, the Nigerian fuel
retailer previously known as African Petroleum Plc, fell after
it reported a 73 percent decline in first-quarter profit.  The stock lost 96 kobo, or 5 percent, to 18.32 naira by the
2:30 p.m. close in Lagos.  Net income retreated to 210.6 million naira ($1 million)
for the three months through March, from 791.4 million naira a
year earlier, the company said in a statement posted on the
website of the  Nigerian Stock Exchange  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos on  at
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 